{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775896060114,"sessionID":"ses_284590c14ffe8XlWT84CyDeEpH","part":{"id":"prt_d7ba751b6001wQl79kH0wNZNbc","messageID":"msg_d7ba738bc001DDMsnIc0vBgRZK","sessionID":"ses_284590c14ffe8XlWT84CyDeEpH","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-024/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-024/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-024: DockerService 封装 — Design Document\n2: \n3: ## Architecture\n4: \n5: ### Component Diagram\n6: ```\n7: ┌─────────────────┐\n8: │   CLI Commands  │\n9: │  (deploy, etc)  │\n10: └────────┬────────┘\n11:          │\n12: ┌────────▼────────┐\n13: │  DockerService  │\n14: │ (docker_service)│\n15: └────────┬────────┘\n16:          │\n17:     ┌────┴────┐\n18:     ▼         ▼\n19: ┌───────┐ ┌───────┐\n20: │Docker │ │Docker │\n21: │ SDK   │ │ CLI   │\n22: └───┬───┘ └───────┘\n23:     │\n24:     ▼\n25: ┌─────────┐\n26: │ Docker  │\n27: │ Daemon  │\n28: └─────────┘\n29: ```\n30: \n31: ## Key Design Decisions\n32: \n33: ### Dual Backend Strategy\n34: - Primary: Docker SDK for Python (docker-py)\n35: - Fallback: Docker CLI subprocess calls\n36: - Automatic detection of available backend\n37: \n38: ### Connection Management\n39: - Support for local Docker socket (unix:///var/run/docker.sock)\n40: - Support for remote Docker daemon via env variables\n41: - Connection pooling for SDK backend\n42: \n43: ### Error Handling\n44: - Custom exception hierarchy for Docker-specific errors\n45: - Structured error messages with actionable suggestions\n46: - Retry logic for transient failures\n47: \n48: ### Async Support\n49: - Async methods for long-running operations (pull, build)\n50: - Callback-based progress reporting\n51: - Timeout configuration per operation\n52: \n53: ## Data Flow\n54: 1. CLI command calls DockerService method\n55: 2. Service validates parameters\n56: 3. Execute via SDK or CLI backend\n57: 4. Parse and structure response\n58: 5. Return result or raise exception\n\n(End of file - total 58 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-024: DockerService 封装 — Design Document\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Component Diagram\n```\n┌─────────────────┐\n│   CLI Commands  │\n│  (deploy, etc)  │\n└────────┬────────┘\n         │\n┌────────▼────────┐\n│  DockerService  │\n│ (docker_service)│\n└────────┬────────┘\n         │\n    ┌────┴────┐\n    ▼         ▼\n┌───────┐ ┌───────┐\n│Docker │ │Docker │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-024/design.md","time":{"start":1775896060079,"end":1775896060113}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775896060118,"sessionID":"ses_284590c14ffe8XlWT84CyDeEpH","part":{"id":"prt_d7ba75827001Bc4pfU03FFTrsA","messageID":"msg_d7ba738bc001DDMsnIc0vBgRZK","sessionID":"ses_284590c14ffe8XlWT84CyDeEpH","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-024: DockerService 封装 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: This document describes the delta specification for implementing the DockerService\n5: encapsulation layer in the cmd/cli module.\n6: \n7: ## Current State\n8: - Docker operations scattered in various places\n9: - No unified abstraction for container management\n10: - Direct subprocess calls to docker CLI in some places\n11: - Limited error handling for Docker operations\n12: \n13: ## Target State\n14: A unified DockerService class that:\n15: - Provides clean abstraction over Docker operations\n16: - Supports both Docker SDK and CLI fallback\n17: - Offers comprehensive error handling\n18: - Returns structured data\n19: - Supports async operations\n20: \n21: ## Delta Analysis\n22: \n23: ### New Components\n24: 1. **DockerService** (`cmd/cli/internal/docker_service.py`)\n25:    - Main service class with all Docker operations\n26:    - Backend selection (SDK/CLI)\n27:    - Connection management\n28: \n29: 2. **Docker Exceptions** (`cmd/cli/internal/docker_exceptions.py`)\n30:    - DockerError base class\n31:    - ConnectionError, ImageNotFoundError, etc.\n32: \n33: 3. **Configuration** (`cmd/cli/internal/docker_config.py`)\n34:    - DockerConnectionConfig dataclass\n35:    - Environment variable parsing\n36: \n37: ### Modified Components\n38: - None (this is a new service layer)\n39: \n40: ### Dependencies\n41: - docker-py library (optional, for SDK backend)\n42: - Existing subprocess utilities for CLI backend\n43: \n44: ## Interface Specification\n45: \n46: ### DockerService Class\n47: ```python\n48: class DockerService:\n49:     def __init__(self, config: DockerConfig = None)\n50:     def create_container(self, image: str, **kwargs) -> Container\n51:     def start_container(self, container_id: str) -> None\n52:     def stop_container(self, container_id: str, timeout: int = 30) -> None\n53:     def remove_container(self, container_id: str, force: bool = False) -> None\n54:     def list_containers(self, all: bool = False) -> List[Container]\n55:     def pull_image(self, image: str, callback: Callable = None) -> Image\n56:     def build_image(self, path: str, tag: str, **kwargs) -> Image\n57:     def list_images(self) -> List[Image]\n58:     def remove_image(self, image_id: str, force: bool = False) -> None\n59: ```\n60: \n61: ## Implementation Notes\n62: - Prefer Docker SDK when available\n63: - Fallback to CLI for operations not supported by SDK\n64: - All methods should accept timeout parameter\n65: - Progress callbacks for long operations\n\n(End of file - total 65 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-024: DockerService 封装 — Delta Spec\n\n## Overview\nThis document describes the delta specification for implementing the DockerService\nencapsulation layer in the cmd/cli module.\n\n## Current State\n- Docker operations scattered in various places\n- No unified abstraction for container management\n- Direct subprocess calls to docker CLI in some places\n- Limited error handling for Docker operations\n\n## Target State\nA unified DockerService class that:\n- Provides clean abstraction over Docker operations\n- Supports both Docker SDK and CLI fallback\n- Offers comprehensive error handling\n- Returns structured data\n- Supports async operations\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775896060081,"end":1775896060115}}}}
