{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775896084054,"sessionID":"ses_284590c14ffe8XlWT84CyDeEpH","part":{"id":"prt_d7ba7ba1d001hl2uMwkmhvuhfr","messageID":"msg_d7ba77ff9001mJQDb8vMOJVjb4","sessionID":"ses_284590c14ffe8XlWT84CyDeEpH","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:13","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: DockerService Encapsulation (AR-024)\n2: \n3: ## AR-024 — DockerService 封装\n4: \n5: | Field | Value |\n6: |-------|-------|\n7: | **Module** | `cmd/cli` |\n8: | **Language** | Python |\n9: | **Size** | M (Medium) |\n10: | **Status** | Proposed |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Purpose\n15: \n16: Implement the `DockerService` class to provide a unified, high-level interface for Docker operations within the AgentCube CLI. This service SHALL abstract Docker SDK interactions for image building, tagging, pushing, and management, providing consistent error handling, logging, and result formatting across the CLI toolchain.\n17: \n18: The `DockerService` SHALL:\n19: - Provide a singleton-style Docker client with connection pooling and health checking\n20: - Support building images from Dockerfiles with customizable build arguments\n21: - Enable image tagging and multi-registry push operations with authentication\n22: - Offer image information retrieval and listing capabilities\n23: - Extract and handle registry credentials from URLs\n24: - Provide consistent error handling with meaningful error messages\n25: \n26: ---\n27: \n28: ## Scope\n29: \n30: ### In Scope\n31: \n32: 1. **DockerService Core Implementation**\n33:    - `DockerService` class in `agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n34:    - Lazy-initialized Docker client with connection health verification\n35:    - Verbose logging support for debugging Docker operations\n36: \n37: 2. **Image Building**\n38:    - `build_image()` method with context path and Dockerfile path parameters\n39:    - Support for build arguments (`build_args`) for proxy configuration\n40:    - Build log streaming and error extraction from Docker build output\n41:    - Build time tracking and image size formatting\n42:    - Result return with image name, ID, size, and build duration\n43: \n44: 3. **Image Tagging**\n45:    - `tag_image()` method for tagging existing images\n46:    - Source and target tag specification\n47:    - Image ID preservation and validation\n48: \n49: 4. **Image Information**\n50:    - `get_image_info()` method to retrieve image details\n51:    - `list_images()` method for listing all or filtered images\n52:    - Size formatting in human-readable format (MB)\n53:    - Image ID truncation for display (12-character format)\n54: \n55: 5. **Image Push with Registry Support**\n56:    - `push_image()` method with optional registry URL\n57:    - Registry authentication via username/password\n58:    - Automatic image retagging for registry pushes\n59:    - Push log streaming and error handling\n60:    - Support for public and private registries\n61: \n62: 6. **Credential Management**\n63:    - `extract_credentials_from_url()` method for parsing embedded credentials\n64:    - URL format: `user:pass@registry.com/image:tag`\n65:    - Automatic credential extraction and URL cleaning\n66:    - URL decoding for special characters in credentials\n67: \n68: 7. **Error Handling**\n69:    - `RuntimeError` for Docker connectivity issues\n70:    - `FileNotFoundError` for missing Dockerfiles or contexts\n71:    - Build error extraction from Docker build logs\n72:    - Push error detection from push log streams\n73:    - Integration with CLI's `_handle_error()` pattern\n74: \n75: ### Out of Scope\n76: \n77: 1. **Docker Compose**: Multi-container orchestration is not supported\n78: 2. **Volume Management**: Docker volume creation and management\n79: 3. **Network Management**: Docker network configuration\n80: 4. **Container Runtime**: Running and managing containers (only image operations)\n81: 5. **Registry Management**: Creating/managing registry repositories\n82: 6. **Image Scanning**: Security scanning of images\n83: 7. **Multi-platform Builds**: Cross-platform image builds (manifests)\n84: 8. **BuildKit Features**: Advanced BuildKit syntax and features\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ## Design\n89: \n90: ### DockerService Class Structure\n91: \n92: ```python\n93: class DockerService:\n94:     \"\"\"Service for Docker image building and management.\"\"\"\n95: \n96:     def __init__(self, verbose: bool = False) -> None: ...\n97:     \"\"\"Initialize DockerService with optional verbose logging.\"\"\"\n98: \n99:     def _get_client(self) -> docker.DockerClient: ...\n100:     \"\"\"Get or create Docker client with health check.\"\"\"\n101: \n102:     def is_docker_available(self) -> bool: ...\n103:     \"\"\"Check if Docker daemon is available and running.\"\"\"\n104: \n105:     def build_image(\n106:         self,\n107:         context_path: Path,\n108:         dockerfile_path: Path,\n109:         image_name: str,\n110:         tag: str,\n111:         build_args: Optional[Dict[str, str]] = None,\n112:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n113:     \"\"\"Build a Docker image from a Dockerfile.\"\"\"\n114: \n115:     def tag_image(\n116:         self,\n117:         image_name: str,\n118:         source_tag: str,\n119:         target_tag: str,\n120:     ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n121:     \"\"\"Tag an existing Docker image.\"\"\"\n122: \n123:     def get_image_info(\n124:         self,\n125:         image_name: str,\n126:         tag: str = \"latest\",\n127:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n128:     \"\"\"Get information about a Docker image.\"\"\"\n129: \n130:     def list_images(\n131:         self,\n132:         name: Optional[str] = None,\n133:     ) -> List[Dict[str, Any]]: ...\n134:     \"\"\"List Docker images, optionally filtered by name.\"\"\"\n135: \n136:     def push_image(\n137:         self,\n138:         image_name: str,\n139:         tag: str = \"latest\",\n140:         registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n141:         username: Optional[str] = None,\n142:         password: Optional[str] = None,\n143:     ) -> Dict[str, Any]: ...\n144:     \"\"\"Push a Docker image to a registry.\"\"\"\n145: \n146:     def extract_credentials_from_url(\n147:         self,\n148:         image_url: str,\n149:     ) -> tuple[str, Optional[str], Optional[str]]: ...\n150:     \"\"\"Extract credentials from image URL with embedded auth.\"\"\"\n151: ```\n152: \n153: ### Build Image Flow\n154: \n155: ```\n156: build_image(context_path, dockerfile_path, image_name, tag, build_args)\n157:     │\n158:     ▼\n159: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n160: │ Validate Paths              │\n161: │ - Check Dockerfile exists   │\n162: │ - Check context exists      │\n163: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n164:               │\n165:               ▼\n166: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n167: │ Get Docker Client           │\n168: │ - from_env()                │\n169: │ - ping() health check       │\n170: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n171:               │\n172:               ▼\n173: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n174: │ Prepare Build Args          │\n175: │ - Relative Dockerfile path  │\n176: │ - Build context path        │\n177: │ - Tag: name:tag             │\n178: │ - Optional build_args       │\n179: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n180:               │\n181:               ▼\n182: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n183: │ Execute Build               │\n184: │ - client.images.build()     │\n185: │ - Stream logs               │\n186: │ - Track duration            │\n187: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n188:               │\n189:               ▼\n190: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n191: │ Handle Build Errors         │\n192: │ - Extract error from logs   │\n193: │ - Raise RuntimeError        │\n194: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n195:               │\n196:               ▼\n197: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n198: │ Format Results              │\n199: │ - Truncate image ID         │\n200: │ - Format size (MB)          │\n201: │ - Calculate build time      │\n202: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n203:               │\n204:               ▼\n205:          Return Result Dict\n206: ```\n207: \n208: ### Push Image Flow\n209: \n210: ```\n211: push_image(image_name, tag, registry_url, username, password)\n212:     │\n213:     ▼\n214: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n215: │ Get Docker Client           │\n216: │ - Verify connectivity       │\n217: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n218:               │\n219:               ▼\n220: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n221: │ Construct Image Names       │\n222: │ - local_tag: name:tag       │\n223: │ - full_name: registry/name  │\n224: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n225:               │\n226:               ▼\n227: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n228: │ Get Local Image             │\n229: │ - client.images.get()       │\n230: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n231:               │\n232:               ▼\n233: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n234: │ Tag for Registry (if needed)│\n235: │ - image.tag(registry/name)  │\n236: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n237:               │\n238:               ▼\n239: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n240: │ Authenticate (if needed)    │\n241: │ - client.login()            │\n242: │ - username/password         │\n243: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n244:               │\n245:               ▼\n246: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n247: │ Push Image                  │\n248: │ - client.images.push()      │\n249: │ - Stream logs               │\n250: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n251:               │\n252:               ▼\n253: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n254: │ Process Push Logs           │\n255: │ - Check for errors          │\n256: │ - Log status updates        │\n257: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n258:               │\n259:               ▼\n260:          Return Push Result\n261: ```\n262: \n263: ### Credential Extraction Flow\n264: \n265: ```\n266: extract_credentials_from_url(image_url)\n267:     │\n268:     ▼\n269: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n270: │ Parse URL                   │\n271: │ - urllib.parse.urlparse()   │\n272: │ - Handle // prefix          │\n273: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n274:               │\n275:               ▼\n276: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n277: │ Extract Components          │\n278: │ - parsed.username           │\n279: │ - parsed.password           │\n280: │ - parsed.hostname           │\n281: │ - parsed.port               │\n282: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n283:               │\n284:               ▼\n285: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n286: │ URL Decode Credentials      │\n287: │ - urllib.parse.unquote()    │\n288: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n289:               │\n290:               ▼\n291: ┌─────────────────────────────┐\n292: │ Reconstruct Clean URL       │\n293: │ - Remove credentials        │\n294: │ - Preserve path/query       │\n295: └─────────────┬───────────────┘\n296:               │\n297:               ▼\n298:     Return (url, user, pass)\n299: ```\n300: \n301: ---\n302: \n303: ## Impact Analysis\n304: \n305: ### Affected Components\n306: \n307: | Component | Impact | Description |\n308: |-----------|--------|-------------|\n309: | `BuildRuntime` | High | Uses `DockerService.build_image()` for local builds |\n310: | `PublishRuntime` | High | Uses `DockerService.push_image()` for registry pushes |\n311: | `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Medium | May export `DockerService` for convenience |\n312: | CLI error handling | Low | Integrates with existing `_handle_error()` pattern |\n313: | Dependencies | Low | Requires `docker>=6.0.0` (already in pyproject.toml) |\n314: \n315: ### Data Format Changes\n316: \n317: **Build Result Format:**\n318: ```python\n319: {\n320:     \"image_name\": str,        # Base image name\n321:     \"image_tag\": str,         # Tag (e.g., \"latest\", \"v1.0.0\")\n322:     \"image_id\": str,          # 12-character truncated ID\n323:     \"image_size\": str,        # Formatted as \"XX.XXMB\"\n324:     \"build_time\": str,        # Formatted as \"X.XX\" seconds\n325:     \"full_tag\": str,          # Complete name:tag\n326: }\n327: ```\n328: \n329: **Push Result Format:**\n330: ```python\n331: {\n332:     \"image_name\": str,        # Full image name with registry\n333:     \"tag\": str,               # Image tag\n334:     \"registry\": Optional[str], # Registry URL (if any)\n335:     \"pushed\": bool,           # Success indicator\n336: }\n337: ```\n338: \n339: **Image Info Format:**\n340: ```python\n341: {\n342:     \"name\": str,              # Image name\n343:     \"tag\": str,               # Image tag\n344:     \"id\": str,                # 12-character truncated ID\n345:     \"size\": str,              # Formatted as \"XX.XXMB\"\n346:     \"created\": str,           # ISO timestamp\n347:     \"labels\": Dict[str, str], # Image labels\n348: }\n349: ```\n350: \n351: ### Error Scenarios\n352: \n353: | Scenario | Exception | Message Pattern |\n354: |----------|-----------|-----------------|\n355: | Docker not running | `RuntimeError` | \"Docker is not available or not running\" |\n356: | Missing Dockerfile | `FileNotFoundError` | \"Dockerfile not found: {path}\" |\n357: | Missing context | `FileNotFoundError` | \"Build context not found: {path}\" |\n358: | Build failure | `RuntimeError` | \"Docker build failed: {error_msg}\" |\n359: | Push failure | `RuntimeError` | \"Failed to push image: {error}\" |\n360: | Image not found | `RuntimeError` | \"Image not found: {full_tag}\" |\n361: | Tag failure | `RuntimeError` | \"Failed to tag image: {error}\" |\n362: \n363: ---\n364: \n365: ## Alternatives Considered\n366: \n367: ### Alternative 1: Direct Docker SDK Usage in Runtimes\n368: \n369: **Approach**: Each runtime class directly imports and uses `docker` module without a service layer.\n370: \n371: **Rejected**: Violates separation of concerns. Duplicates client initialization logic, error handling, and logging configuration. Makes testing harder due to scattered Docker dependencies.\n372: \n373: ### Alternative 2: Subprocess-based Docker CLI\n374: \n375: **Approach**: Use `subprocess.run()` to execute `docker` CLI commands instead of SDK.\n376: \n377: **Rejected**: Loses programmatic access to build/push logs. Harder to parse structured output. Requires Docker CLI to be installed (SDK only requires Docker daemon). Less type-safe.\n378: \n379: ### Alternative 3: Async Docker Client\n380: \n381: **Approach**: Use `aiodocker` for fully asynchronous Docker operations.\n382: \n383: **Partially Accepted**: Current implementation uses synchronous SDK which is sufficient for CLI operations. Async operations can be wrapped in `asyncio.to_thread()` if needed for concurrent operations in the future.\n384: \n385: ### Alternative 4: Podman Compatibility Layer\n386: \n387: **Approach**: Abstract over Docker and Podman APIs for broader compatibility.\n388: \n389: **Deferred**: Adds complexity. Podman claims Docker API compatibility; can be tested later. Current focus is on Docker-only environments as per requirements.\n390: \n391: ### Alternative 5: External Build Service\n392: \n393: **Approach**: Delegate builds to an external build service (e.g., BuildKit daemon, cloud builder).\n394: \n395: **Rejected**: Overkill for current requirements. Local Docker builds are sufficient for the CLI use case. Cloud builds are handled separately in `BuildRuntime._build_cloud()`.\n396: \n397: ---\n398: \n399: ## Verification\n400: \n401: ### Docker Availability Check\n402: \n403: ```python\n404: from agentcube.services.docker_service import DockerService\n405: \n406: service = DockerService(verbose=True)\n407: if service.is_docker_available():\n408:     print(\"Docker is running\")\n409: else:\n410:     print(\"Docker is not available\")\n411: ```\n412: \n413: ### Image Building Verification\n414: \n415: ```python\n416: from pathlib import Path\n417: from agentcube.services.docker_service import DockerService\n418: \n419: service = DockerService(verbose=True)\n420: \n421: # Basic build\n422: result = service.build_image(\n423:     context_path=Path(\"/tmp/test-agent\"),\n424:     dockerfile_path=Path(\"/tmp/test-agent/Dockerfile\"),\n425:     image_name=\"test-agent\",\n426:     tag=\"v1.0.0\",\n427: )\n428: print(f\"Built: {result['full_tag']} ({result['image_id']})\")\n429: \n430: # Build with proxy args\n431: result = service.build_image(\n432:     context_path=Path(\"/tmp/test-agent\"),\n433:     dockerfile_path=Path(\"/tmp/test-agent/Dockerfile\"),\n434:     image_name=\"test-agent\",\n435:     tag=\"latest\",\n436:     build_args={\n437:         \"HTTP_PROXY\": \"http://proxy.example.com:8080\",\n438:         \"HTTPS_PROXY\": \"http://proxy.example.com:8080\",\n439:     },\n440: )\n441: ```\n442: \n443: ### Image Tagging Verification\n444: \n445: ```python\n446: result = service.tag_image(\n447:     image_name=\"test-agent\",\n448:     source_tag=\"latest\",\n449:     target_tag=\"v1.0.0\",\n450: )\n451: print(f\"Tagged: {result['source']} -> {result['target']}\")\n452: ```\n453: \n454: ### Image Information Verification\n455: \n456: ```python\n457: # Get single image info\n458: info = service.get_image_info(\"test-agent\", \"latest\")\n459: print(f\"Size: {info['size']}, Created: {info['created']}\")\n460: \n461: # List all images\n462: images = service.list_images()\n463: for img in images:\n464:     print(f\"{img['name']}:{img['tag']} - {img['size']}\")\n465: \n466: # Filtered list\n467: images = service.list_images(name=\"test-agent\")\n468: ```\n469: \n470: ### Push Verification\n471: \n472: ```python\n473: # Push to default registry (Docker Hub)\n474: result = service.push_image(\"test-agent\", \"latest\")\n475: \n476: # Push to private registry with auth\n477: result = service.push_image(\n478:     image_name=\"test-agent\",\n479:     tag=\"v1.0.0\",\n480:     registry_url=\"registry.example.com\",\n481:     username=\"myuser\",\n482:     password=\"mypass\",\n483: )\n484: print(f\"Pushed to: {result['image_name']}\")\n485: ```\n486: \n487: ### Credential Extraction Verification\n488: \n489: ```python\n490: # URL with embedded credentials\n491: url = \"user:pass@registry.example.com/myimage:tag\"\n492: clean_url, username, password = service.extract_credentials_from_url(url)\n493: print(f\"URL: {clean_url}\")\n494: print(f\"User: {username}\")\n495: print(f\"Pass: {password}\")\n496: # Output: registry.example.com/myimage:tag, user, pass\n497: \n498: # URL with encoded credentials\n499: url = \"user%40domain:p%40ss%23@registry.example.com/image:tag\"\n500: clean_url, username, password = service.extract_credentials_from_url(url)\n501: print(f\"User: {username}\")  # user@domain\n502: print(f\"Pass: {password}\")  # p@ss#\n503: \n504: # URL without credentials\n505: url = \"registry.example.com/image:tag\"\n506: clean_url, username, password = service.extract_credentials_from_url(url)\n507: print(f\"URL: {clean_url}\")  # registry.example.com/image:tag\n508: print(f\"User: {username}\")  # None\n509: ```\n510: \n511: ### Error Handling Verification\n512: \n513: ```python\n514: # Test Docker unavailable\n515: try:\n516:     service = DockerService()\n517:     service._get_client()  # Should raise if Docker not running\n518: except RuntimeError as e:\n519:     print(f\"Expected error: {e}\")\n520: \n521: # Test missing Dockerfile\n522: try:\n523:     service.build_image(\n524:         context_path=Path(\"/tmp\"),\n525:         dockerfile_path=Path(\"/tmp/nonexistent/Dockerfile\"),\n526:         image_name=\"test\",\n527:         tag=\"latest\",\n528:     )\n529: except FileNotFoundError as e:\n530:     print(f\"Expected error: {e}\")\n531: \n532: # Test missing image\n533: try:\n534:     service.get_image_info(\"nonexistent-image\", \"latest\")\n535: except RuntimeError as e:\n536:     print(f\"Expected error: {e}\")\n537: ```\n538: \n539: ---\n540: \n541: ## References\n542: \n543: - [cli-toolkit/design.md](cli-toolkit/design.md) — CLI package layout and service architecture\n544: - [cli-toolkit/spec.md](cli-toolkit/spec.md) — Docker integration requirements specification\n545: - [Docker SDK for Python](https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/) — Official Docker SDK documentation\n546: - AR-020 — CLI Pack Command (uses DockerService for Dockerfile generation)\n547: - AR-021 — CLI Build Command (uses DockerService.build_image())\n548: - AR-022 — CLI Publish Command (uses DockerService.push_image())\n549: - AR-023 — CLI Invoke/Status Commands — Predecessor using service pattern\n550: \n551: ---\n552: \n553: ## Success Criteria\n554: \n555: 1. ✅ `DockerService` class is implemented in `agentcube/services/docker_service.py`\n556: 2. ✅ `_get_client()` lazy-initializes Docker client and performs health check via `ping()`\n557: 3. ✅ `is_docker_available()` returns `True` when Docker daemon is accessible\n558: 4. ✅ `build_image()` builds images from Dockerfile with context path\n559: 5. ✅ Build failures extract and report specific error messages from build logs\n560: 6. ✅ `build_image()` supports optional `build_args` dictionary\n561: 7. ✅ Build results include: `image_name`, `image_tag`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`, `full_tag`\n562: 8. ✅ `tag_image()` creates new tags from existing images\n563: 9. ✅ `get_image_info()` retrieves image details including size, creation time, labels\n564: 10. ✅ `list_images()` returns all images or filters by name\n565: 11. ✅ Image sizes are formatted as \"XX.XXMB\" in results\n566: 12. ✅ Image IDs are truncated to 12 characters for display\n567: 13. ✅ `push_image()` pushes to default registry (Docker Hub)\n568: 14. ✅ `push_image()` supports custom `registry_url` with automatic retagging\n569: 15. ✅ `push_image()` authenticates to registry when `username` and `password` provided\n570: 16. ✅ Push failures are detected from push log streams\n571: 17. ✅ `extract_credentials_from_url()` parses credentials from `user:pass@host` format\n572: 18. ✅ Credentials are URL-decoded (handle `@`, `#`, etc.)\n573: 19. ✅ Clean URL is returned with credentials removed\n574: 20. ✅ All methods use structured logging with `self.logger`\n575: 21. ✅ Verbose mode enables DEBUG level logging\n576: 22. ✅ Docker connection failures raise `RuntimeError` with clear message\n577: 23. ✅ Missing files raise `FileNotFoundError` with path information\n578: 24. ✅ All errors include original exception via `from e` chaining\n579: 25. ✅ `DockerService` is importable from `agentcube.services`\n580: \n581: ---\n582: \n583: *AR-024 — Module: cmd/cli — Language: Python — Size: M*\n\n(End of file - total 583 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: DockerService Encapsulation (AR-024)\n\n## AR-024 — DockerService 封装\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `cmd/cli` |\n| **Language** | Python |\n| **Size** | M (Medium) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the `DockerService` class to provide a unified, high-level interface for Docker operations within the AgentCube CLI. This service SHALL abstract Docker SDK interactions for image building, tagging, pushing, and management, providing consistent error handling, logging, and result formatting across the CLI toolchain.\n\nThe `DockerService` SHALL:\n- Provide a singleton-style Docker client with connection pooling and health checking\n- Support building images from Dockerfiles with customizable build arguments","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775896084033,"end":1775896084051}}}}
